type="user">jms-006Y</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-006Y.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="The git distributed version control system">The <fr:link
href="https://git-scm.com/"
type="external">git</fr:link> distributed version control system</fr:title><fr:taxon>Requirement</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>It is best practice to maintain your <fr:link
href="tfmt-000R.xml"
title="Forests and trees of evergreen notes"
addr="tfmt-000R"
type="local">forest</fr:link> inside of <fr:link
href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Distributed_version_control"
type="external">distributed version control</fr:link>. This serves not only as a way to prevent data loss (because you will be pushing frequently to a remote repository); it also allows you to easily roll back to an earlier version of your <fr:link
href="tfmt-000R.xml"
title="Forests and trees of evergreen notes"
addr="tfmt-000R"
type="local">forest</fr:link>, or to create “branches” in which you prepare <fr:link
href="tfmt-000R.xml"
title="Forests and trees of evergreen notes"
addr="tfmt-000R"
type="local">trees</fr:link> that are not yet ready to be integrated into the <fr:link
href="tfmt-000R.xml"
title="Forests and trees of evergreen notes"
addr="tfmt-000R"
type="local">forest</fr:link>.</fr:p><fr:p>The recommended <fr:link
href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Distributed_version_control"
type="external">distributed version control</fr:link> system is <fr:link
href="https://git-scm.com/"
type="external">git</fr:link>, which comes preinstalled on many unix-based systems and is easy to install otherwise. <fr:link
href="https://git-scm.com/"
type="external">Git</fr:link> is not the most user-friendly piece of software, unfortunately, but it is ubiquitous. It is possible (but not recommended) to use <fr:link
href="jms-005P.xml"
title="Forester"
addr="jms-005P"
type="local">Forester</fr:link> without version control, but note that the simplest way to <fr:link
href="jms-006X.xml"
title="Setting up your forest from the template"
addr="jms-006X"
type="local">initialize your own <fr:link
href="tfmt-000R.xml"
title="Forests and trees of evergreen notes"
addr="tfmt-000R"
type="local">forest</fr:link></fr:link> involves cloning a <fr:link
href="https://git-scm.com/"
type="external">git</fr:link> repository.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
